summary:
9. Urges Member States and the United Nations system to ensure the participation and leadership of women and womenâ€™s organizations in developing strategies to counter terrorism.
The Security Council:

welcomes focus on inclusive prevention efforts against violent extremism, encourages the Secretary-General's Plan to integrate women's participation, leadership and empowerment, and calls for adequate financing;

urges Member States to strengthen access to justice for women in conflict and post-conflict situations, including investigation, prosecution, and punishment of perpetrators of sexual violence;

encourages empowering women to participate in efforts to prevent and combat illicit transfer of small arms and light weapons;

calls for due consideration of the Women, Peace and Security agenda in the World Humanitarian Summit, and integration of gender considerations in humanitarian programming;

invites the Secretary-General to report on progress made on the High-level Review of resolution 1325, including new commitments and monitoring arrangements;

decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
